<subSubSection id="C31B3B9ED23C0272FFD0F8D5546B3212" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBE6815D23C0272FFD0F8D550AC3468" blockId="51.[121,760,1746,1910]" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833">
<taxonomicName id="4C011396D23C0272FFD0F8D5508D3427" box="[121,399,1825,1849]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Limosilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="pontis">
<emphasis id="B975B407D23C0272FFD0F8D5508D3427" box="[121,399,1825,1849]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833">Limosilactobacillus pontis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(pon’tis. L. gen. n. 
<taxonomicName id="4C011396D23C0272FDD1F8D653BA3427" box="[632,696,1826,1849]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Limosilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="pontis">
<emphasis id="B975B407D23C0272FDD1F8D653BA3427" box="[632,696,1826,1849]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833">pontis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of a bridge, referring to BRIDGE, which was the acronym of an EU funded research project).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE6815D23C0272FFD0F878546B3212" blockId="51.[121,688,1931,1956]" lastBlockId="51.[826,1468,183,268]" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833">
Basonym: 
<taxonomicName id="4C011396D23C0272FF41F878536934BA" authority="Vogel et al. 1994" authorityName="Vogel" authorityYear="1994" box="[232,619,1932,1956]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="pontis">
<emphasis id="B975B407D23C0272FF41F87850B434BA" box="[232,438,1932,1956]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833">Lactobacillus pontis</emphasis>
Vogel 
<emphasis id="B975B407D23C0272FE57F879532834BA" box="[510,554,1932,1956]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</taxonomicName>
, 228 
<superScript id="7C74C55DD23C0272FD35F87F53B23487" attach="none" box="[668,688,1931,1945]" fontSize="6" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833">VP</superScript>
Not all strains of 
<taxonomicName id="4C011396D23C0272FC50FF43555633D0" box="[1017,1108,183,206]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="pontis">
<emphasis id="B975B407D23C0272FC50FF43555633D0" box="[1017,1108,183,206]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833">L. pontis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ferment glucose [
<bibRefCitation id="EF9015E4D23C0272FABFFF43544133D1" author="Vogel RF &amp; Bocker G &amp; Stolz P &amp; Ehrmann M &amp; Fanta D" box="[1302,1347,183,207]" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833" pagination="223 - 229" refId="ref71411" refString="267. Vogel RF, Bocker G, Stolz P, Ehrmann M, Fanta D et al. Identification of lactobacilli from sourdough and description of Lactobacillus pontis sp. nov. Int J Syst Bacteriol 1994; 44: 223 - 229." type="journal article" year="1994">267</bibRefCitation>
]; growth is observed at 15 and at 45 °C. The genome sizeof the type strain is 1.67 Mbp. The mol% G+C content of DNA is 43.5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31B3B9ED23C0272FC95FED6540B3101" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBE6815D23C0272FC95FED654623288" blockId="51.[827,1466,290,406]" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833">
Isolated from type Iand type II sourdough but also as typical representatives of the intestinal microbiota of swine [
<bibRefCitation id="EF9015E4D23C0272FA27FEB454AD3246" author="Leser TD &amp; Amenuvor JZ &amp; Jensen TK &amp; Lindecrona RH &amp; Boye M" box="[1422,1455,320,344]" pageId="51" pageNumber="2833" pagination="673 - 690" refId="ref62491" refString="76. Leser TD, Amenuvor JZ, Jensen TK, Lindecrona RH, Boye M et al. Culture-Independent analysis of gut bacteria: the pig gastrointestinal tract microbiota revisited. Appl Environ Microbiol 2002; 68: 673 - 690." type="journal article" year="2002">76</bibRefCitation>
]. Other sources of isolation include silage, dairy products, mezcal fermentation and wet wheat distillers' grain.
</paragraph>
